channel.title: The JavaFire Project (NOT YOUR USUAL RSPS)
channel.description:
[img]http://javafire.99k.org/ryewwre.png[/img]
This project is still only in its beta stage so it is still in development! If you want to join in beta testing or our programming group you may!
What is this? well so far i have figured out a way to run webclients without the difficulty of having to code them, you don't even have to mess with the client source itself! Well only 12 1/2 hours later i have now developed a formula for webSERVERS! these servers are still in the EXTREME stage of beta testing but so far i think they work. What would this mean for rsps? It would mean that you could upload your server to a website and not have to worry about having to port forward! If you want to see my tutorial for the clients just use my website, http://javafire.99k.org/Web%20Client.html.
So far here is some other ideas we could work with if i get this working. Server testing - allowing others to test servers without having to download a million sources to get the right one. Client testing - mostly the same as server testing. A server testing and rating system - this will allow users to rate and test servers, you know how it's just annoying to go through those suckish server advertisements everyday with spam mixed in the download threads? well if my theory is correct we will be able to skip that and just go onto the servers with a new download system, this would consist of something a little like file uploading and downloading along with testing and rating. (more to come :D)
